      "title": "“I’ve always been shy. A little insecure, the kind of person who keeps to himself. Then, a year and a half ago, my family and I bought a restaurant in a medieval village called Finalborgo. Suddenly, my job was talking to strangers every single day. The four of us run Il Guercio together: my mother and I in the dining room, my father and brother in the kitchen. The village is tiny, but the whole world passes through it. Climbers, cyclists, travelers. Everyone tells me, ‘You’re so lucky to work with your family.’ And it’s true. But my brother and I work together and live together. Sometimes it can be a lot. Looking at these photos, I realize I never brought the camera home. Every single one was taken at the restaurant, because right now, the restaurant is my life. It’s harder than I expected, but I have no intention of stopping. My dream is to retire my parents without a single worry. After that, who knows.” — Andrea Finalborgo, Italy Life on Film Translated from Italian and edite",
      "date": "3 hours ago"
